name: Glacial Ray
oracle_text:
Glacial Ray deals 2 damage to any target.
Splice onto Arcane {1}{R} (As you cast an Arcane spell, you may reveal this card from your hand and pay its splice cost. If you do, add this card's effects to that spell.)

name: Goblin Mime
oracle_text: When you speak, sacrifice this creature.
flavor_text: Mung noticed a few clouds gathering in the sky. Perhaps today he could perform his "walking against the wind" routine.

name: Granny's Payback
oracle_text: You gain life equal to your age.
flavor_text: Few remember the exploits of Dakkon's grandmother, Eunice Blackblade.

name: Darksteel Ingot
oracle_text:
Indestructible (Effects that say "destroy" don't destroy this artifact.)
{T}: Add one mana of any color.

name: Mise
oracle_text: Choose a nonland card name, then reveal the top card of your library. If that card has the chosen name, you draw three cards.
flavor_text: Statistically mind-staggering as it might seem, the term "mise" was in fact coined simultaneously by over one thousand Magic players.

name: Ashnod's Coupon
oracle_text: {T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Target player gets you target drink. You pay any costs for the drink.
flavor_text: Limited time offer. Void where prohibited. Limit one per purchase. Valid only in participating duels. This coupon is nontransferable and invalid if shattered, crumbled, detonated, pillaged, or otherwise disenchanted. Cash value less than 1/20 of a cent. Offer not valid in Quebec, Rhode Island, or where prohibited by law or the DCI.

name: Circle of Protection: Art
oracle_text:
As this enchantment enters, choose an artist.
{1}{W}: The next time a source of your choice with art by the chosen artist would deal damage to you this turn, prevent that damage.
{1}{W}: Return this enchantment to its owner's hand.

name: Booster Tutor
oracle_text: Open a sealed Magic booster pack, reveal the cards, and put one of them into your hand. (Remove that card from your deck before beginning a new game.)
flavor_text: Make your judgment wisely: The right pack will let you defeat your nemesis, but a poor choice can only end in torment. And *Homelands*.
